notesStmt.note: This workshop discussion is part of a European student conference. It takes place among students from various different European universities and deals with values that they consider most important for human life. At the beginning, the participants introduce themselves and name three keywords to describe themselves. Then the 'value contest' starts. First, participants work on their own and specify five values. Then, they share their views with a partner; subsequently they discuss them in groups of four and eight students. Afterwards, representatives are chosen for each of these groups who negotiate the five most important values for the whole group. For that purpose they leave the room and continue their discussion in a separate room. The five values they agreed on are then presented and discussed in front of the whole group. Generally, the working atmosphere is very good. The discussions are highly animated and chaired by S4 and S15.

equipment.p: Portable minidisc recorder with electret condenser stereo microphone
